General.Name: Stalexport Autostrady SA
General.Description: Stalexport Autostrady S.A., together with its subsidiaries, constructs and operates motorways in Poland. The company operates and maintains Katowice-Kraków section of the A4 motorway. It also engages in the construction of roads and railroad; management and business advisory business; and rental services. The company was formerly known as STALEXPORT S.A. and changed its name to Stalexport Autostrady S.A. in September 2007. Stalexport Autostrady S.A. was founded in 1963 and is based in Myslowice, Poland.
